#Approach:

Single Number – XOR Approach

Is problem me har element do baar aata hai aur sirf ek element ek hi baar aata hai.
Hum XOR use karte hain kyunki XOR me same numbers cancel ho jate hain.

Important XOR properties:
a ^ a = 0
a ^ 0 = a

Agar hum array ke saare elements ka XOR karein, to jo numbers do baar aayenge wo cancel ho jayenge
aur jo number ek baar aaya hai wahi answer bachega.

Isliye hum ek variable me sab elements ka XOR karte hain aur final XOR hi single number hota hai.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int singleNumber(int[] nums) {
        int xor = 0;

        for(int i=0; i<nums.length; i++){
            xor = xor ^ nums[i];
        }
        return xor;
    }
}
